  <p id="Bl0fwk">Previous versions of watchOS allowed the Apple Watch to be used as a remote control for the Apple TV with limited functionality. With <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/9/16/24246171/apple-watchos-11-watch-sleep-apnea-smartwatch-launch">watchOS 11</a>, the smartwatch can potentially completely replace the <a href="https://www.theverge.com/22446699/apple-tv-4k-hd-siri-remote-review-features-price">Siri Remote</a> that now ships with Apple’s streaming box, with new capabilities <a href="https://9to5mac.com/2024/09/19/your-apple-watch-can-now-replace-your-tv-remote/">spotted by 9to5Mac</a>.</p>
<p id="LXGNXs">Before <a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24170653/apple-watch-watchos-11-features-updates-wwdc">watchOS 11</a>, the Apple Watch’s Remote app could only be used to play and pause videos, or navigate tvOS using swipe gestures to move through menus and screen taps to make selections. It was useful if you couldn’t reach the Apple TV’s remote, but couldn’t replace its features entirely.</p>
